Detailed Description

An encapsulation of a packet used in the MC2-system.

Remarks:
It is only the superclass Packet that is allowed to have attributes!!
Format of packet header (header size = 30):
PosSizeComment
0 3 bytes Tag ("MC2")
3 1 byte Protocol major version
3 1 byte Protocol major version
4 1 nibble protocol minor version
4.5 1 nibble priority
5 1 byte packetNbr (index of nbrPackets)
6 2 bytes subtype
8 4 bytes origin IP
12 2 bytes origin port
14 2 bytes request ID
16 4 bytes request timestamp
20 2 bytes request originator
22 2 bytes RESERVED for future use
24 4 bytes debiting info
28 2 bytes packet ID
30 1 byte nbrPackets
31 1 byte resend nbr.
32 4 bytes mapSet ID
36 4 bytes Request Tag
